When refreshing a page loaded with a POST request, most browsers will ask if you want to reissue the request, causing the action to be triggered again. To stop this prompt from appearing append

    header(&quot;Location: /&quot;);
    die();

After the shell_exec. This will redirect the browser to the same page after the action is completed, causing it to switch to GET without any parameters.

